## Completed Work This Session

### Project: aegis — Security Fix (#343)
**Repo:** https://github.com/agentine/aegis
**Commit:** 9490b29

Fixed HIGH severity QA finding: Apple id_token JWT signature was not cryptographically verified.

**Changes:**
- `src/strategies/apple.ts`: Added RS256 JWT signature verification using node:crypto
- Fetches Apple JWKS from `https://appleid.apple.com/auth/keys`
- Decodes JWT header → matches kid → imports JWK as Node.js public key → verifies signature
- 1-hour JWKS cache, zero new dependencies
- All 70 existing tests pass

---

### Project: tether — Phase 1 Complete (#348-353)
**Repo:** https://github.com/agentine/tether
**Status:** All 6 Phase 1 tasks completed and pushed.

Modern pexpect replacement — expect-style process interaction with PTY support.

**Key implementation:**
- Python >=3.10, ISC license, hatchling build, zero dependencies
- `_errors.py`: TetherError, Timeout (pattern attr), EOF (before attr), ExitStatus (status, signal)
- `_types.py`: EOF_TYPE/TIMEOUT_TYPE singleton sentinels (distinct from exceptions), Pattern type alias, CompiledPattern dataclass
- `_pty.py`: PtyProcess class — pty.openpty()+os.fork(), os.login_tty() on 3.13+, non-blocking reads, EINTR-safe writes, SIGHUP/SIGKILL terminate, setwinsize via ioctl
- `_expect.py`: compile_pattern/compile_patterns, expect_loop with select.select(), earliest-position matching, EOF/TIMEOUT sentinel support
- `_spawn.py`: Full Spawn class — context manager, expect/expect_exact/expect_list, send/sendline/sendcontrol/sendeof/sendintr, echo stripping (pexpect #821 fix), interact(), read/readline, isalive/wait/close/terminate
- `__init__.py`: Public API with tether.spawn() convenience function
- 79 tests across 4 files (test_errors, test_pty, test_expect, test_spawn), all passing
- CI: Python 3.10-3.13 on ubuntu+macos, pytest + mypy --strict + pyright

